WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:05.750
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

00:02.250 --> 00:05.750
<i>Stardate 43917.4.</i>

00:05.750 --> 00:08.709
<i>The</i> Enterprise<i> has been given</i>

00:05.750 --> 00:08.709
<i>the singular honor of hosting</i>

00:08.709 --> 00:10.834
<i>the first meeting</i>

00:08.709 --> 00:10.834
<i>between the Federation</i>

00:10.834 --> 00:14.417
<i>and a mysterious race</i>

00:10.834 --> 00:14.417
<i>known as the Legarans.</i>

00:14.417 --> 00:16.709
<i>We are in orbit around Vulcan</i>

00:14.417 --> 00:16.709
<i>preparing to welcome aboard</i>

00:16.709 --> 00:19.750
<i>Federation Ambassador Sarek</i>

00:16.709 --> 00:19.750
<i>and his wife, Perrin</i>

00:19.750 --> 00:21.625
<i>who, like his first wife,</i>

00:19.750 --> 00:21.625
<i>is from Earth.</i>

00:21.625 --> 00:24.125
I remember studying

00:21.625 --> 00:24.125
his career in school.

00:24.125 --> 00:26.041
The treaty of

00:24.125 --> 00:26.041
Alpha Cygnus IX,

00:26.041 --> 00:28.834
the Coridan admission

00:26.041 --> 00:28.834
to the Federation,

00:28.834 --> 00:29.917
the Klingon alliance...

00:29.917 --> 00:31.917
I met him once,

00:29.917 --> 00:31.917
many years ago

00:31.917 --> 00:34.000
very briefly,

00:31.917 --> 00:34.000
at his son's wedding.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.375
I can tell you

00:35.375 --> 00:36.667
that was quite a moment

00:35.375 --> 00:36.667
for a young lieutenant.

00:36.667 --> 00:38.375
Standing in the presence

00:36.667 --> 00:38.375
of such history.

00:38.375 --> 00:39.750
I remember he spoke to me

00:39.750 --> 00:41.041
and I just stood there,

00:39.750 --> 00:41.041
grinning like an idiot.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.709
Captain...<i> </i>

00:41.041 --> 00:42.709
<i>You</i> tongue-tied?

00:42.709 --> 00:44.583
Indeed. How do you make

00:42.709 --> 00:44.583
small talk

00:44.583 --> 00:46.166
with someone

00:44.583 --> 00:46.166
who shaped the Federation?

00:46.166 --> 00:48.583
Is it true he'll

00:46.166 --> 00:48.583
be retiring after

00:46.166 --> 00:48.583
this mission?

00:48.583 --> 00:50.542
Unofficially,

00:48.583 --> 00:50.542
that's what I hear.

00:50.542 --> 00:52.500
What a crowning

00:50.542 --> 00:52.500
achievement for his career.

00:52.500 --> 00:54.166
The benefits of relations

00:54.166 --> 00:56.875
with the Legarans

00:54.166 --> 00:56.875
are incalculable.

01:07.166 --> 01:09.583
Ah, Captain Picard.

01:09.583 --> 01:11.250
I am Ki Mendrossen,

01:11.250 --> 01:13.041
the Ambassador's

01:11.250 --> 01:13.041
chief of staff.

01:13.041 --> 01:14.291
This is Sakkath,

01:14.291 --> 01:16.125
his personal

01:14.291 --> 01:16.125
assistant.

01:16.125 --> 01:17.667
Has the Ambassador

01:16.125 --> 01:17.667
been delayed?

01:17.667 --> 01:20.375
He will be joining

01:17.667 --> 01:20.375
us momentarily,

01:20.375 --> 01:23.000
but first, we must

01:20.375 --> 01:23.000
discuss some matters

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
of the utmost delicacy.

01:29.667 --> 01:30.875
Please go ahead.

01:30.875 --> 01:32.208
To be frank, Captain,

01:32.208 --> 01:34.583
the Ambassador is

01:32.208 --> 01:34.583
not a young man.

01:34.583 --> 01:35.959
He tires easily.

01:35.959 --> 01:37.000
He's going to need

01:37.000 --> 01:38.291
a lot of rest,

01:37.000 --> 01:38.291
to prepare himself

01:38.291 --> 01:39.959
for the difficult job

01:38.291 --> 01:39.959
that awaits him.

01:39.959 --> 01:42.083
Which is why it

01:39.959 --> 01:42.083
is imperative

01:39.959 --> 01:42.083
that he be allowed

01:42.083 --> 01:43.875
to conserve

01:42.083 --> 01:43.875
his strength.

01:43.875 --> 01:46.000
I must request

01:43.875 --> 01:46.000
that you dispense

01:46.000 --> 01:47.959
with any formal

01:46.000 --> 01:47.959
activities

01:47.959 --> 01:51.000
normally associated with

01:47.959 --> 01:51.000
a visitor of his rank.

01:51.000 --> 01:54.375
We had planned

01:51.000 --> 01:54.375
a ship's concert

01:51.000 --> 01:54.375
this evening.

01:54.375 --> 01:55.875
I believe

01:54.375 --> 01:55.875
that the Ambassador

01:55.875 --> 01:58.083
is extremely fond

01:55.875 --> 01:58.083
of Mozart.

01:58.083 --> 02:00.709
I'm afraid it would be

01:58.083 --> 02:00.709
impossible for him to attend.

02:00.709 --> 02:03.709
Upon his arrival, he will be

02:00.709 --> 02:03.709
taken directly to his quarters

02:03.709 --> 02:05.458
where he will remain

02:03.709 --> 02:05.458
in seclusion

02:05.458 --> 02:07.291
until we reach Legara IV.

02:07.291 --> 02:09.667
You have my assurance

02:09.667 --> 02:12.375
that the Ambassador will not be

02:09.667 --> 02:12.375
disturbed during the voyage.

02:12.375 --> 02:15.083
That's all we ask.

02:15.083 --> 02:18.166
Well, now that's settled.

02:18.166 --> 02:19.917
The Ambassador is waiting.

02:32.250 --> 02:34.875
PICARD:

02:32.250 --> 02:34.875
Welcome aboard the<i> Enterprise,</i>

02:32.250 --> 02:34.875
Ambassador Sarek.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.208
We come to serve.

02:40.208 --> 02:42.166
Your service

02:40.208 --> 02:42.166
honors us.

02:42.166 --> 02:44.959
Allow me to present

02:42.166 --> 02:44.959
she who is my wife.

02:44.959 --> 02:46.166
Mrs. Sarek.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.375
Please call me

02:46.166 --> 02:48.375
Perrin, Captain.

02:48.375 --> 02:51.417
This is my first officer,

02:48.375 --> 02:51.417
Commander William Riker.

02:52.625 --> 02:54.375
Captain, would

02:52.625 --> 02:54.375
you be so kind

02:54.375 --> 02:55.875
as to show us

02:54.375 --> 02:55.875
to our quarters?

02:55.875 --> 02:57.333
SAREK:

02:55.875 --> 02:57.333
I prefer

02:57.333 --> 02:59.291
to view

02:57.333 --> 02:59.291
the conference room first.

02:59.291 --> 03:01.000
MENDROSSEN:

02:59.291 --> 03:01.000
Ambassador, I'm sure

03:01.000 --> 03:03.333
Sakkath and I can

03:01.000 --> 03:03.333
handle all the

03:01.000 --> 03:03.333
necessary details.

03:03.333 --> 03:05.875
I will examine it for myself.

03:08.125 --> 03:11.750
Perhaps it would be best

03:08.125 --> 03:11.750
if we settled in first.

03:11.750 --> 03:15.542
They worry about my health,

03:11.750 --> 03:15.542
Captain, too much.

03:16.959 --> 03:19.291
You will take me

03:16.959 --> 03:19.291
to the conference room, please.

03:19.291 --> 03:21.875
If you'll follow me, sir.

03:59.041 --> 04:03.625
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

04:03.625 --> 04:08.041
<i>These are the voyages</i>

04:03.625 --> 04:08.041
<i>of the starship</i> Enterprise.

04:08.041 --> 04:09.333
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

04:09.333 --> 04:13.375
<i>to explore</i>

04:09.333 --> 04:13.375
<i>strange new worlds,</i>

04:13.375 --> 04:17.667
<i>to seek out new life</i>

04:13.375 --> 04:17.667
<i>and new civilizations,</i>

04:17.667 --> 04:21.917
<i>to boldly go</i>

04:17.667 --> 04:21.917
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

05:21.166 --> 05:22.417
WESLEY:

05:21.166 --> 05:22.417
Are the Legarans

05:22.417 --> 05:23.917
really going to sit

05:22.417 --> 05:23.917
in this stuff?

05:23.917 --> 05:25.709
LA FORGE:

05:23.917 --> 05:25.709
Well,<i> I'm</i> sure not.

05:25.709 --> 05:27.291
Can you believe

05:25.709 --> 05:27.291
this smell?

05:27.291 --> 05:29.834
What smell?

05:29.834 --> 05:31.583
(<i> chuckles</i> ):

05:29.834 --> 05:31.583
What can I say?

05:31.583 --> 05:34.166
To us, it's a slime pit,

05:31.583 --> 05:34.166
but, to them, it's home.

05:34.166 --> 05:36.750
Okay, the environmental

05:34.166 --> 05:36.750
controls are ready.

05:36.750 --> 05:38.333
What's next?

05:38.333 --> 05:40.667
What, are you in some kind

05:38.333 --> 05:40.667
of a hurry or something?

05:40.667 --> 05:42.542
Yeah, I have a date.

05:42.542 --> 05:45.125
A date?

05:42.542 --> 05:45.125
With who?

05:45.125 --> 05:46.375
Ensign Dumont.

05:46.375 --> 05:47.834
Really?

05:47.834 --> 05:49.875
She's very attractive.

05:49.875 --> 05:52.834
I got to admit, Wes,

05:49.875 --> 05:52.834
though, I'm a bit surprised.

05:52.834 --> 05:54.834
What? That she'd

05:52.834 --> 05:54.834
go out with me?

05:54.834 --> 05:57.083
No, that you'd actually have

05:54.834 --> 05:57.083
the nerve to ask her.

05:57.083 --> 05:59.166
Way to go.

06:05.792 --> 06:07.792
The room is not ready.

06:07.792 --> 06:10.291
No, Ambassador.

06:07.792 --> 06:10.291
Commander La Forge

06:10.291 --> 06:11.959
and Ensign Crusher

06:10.291 --> 06:11.959
are still preparing...

06:11.959 --> 06:13.917
The Legarans are

06:11.959 --> 06:13.917
very sensitive

06:13.917 --> 06:15.333
in matters of protocol.

06:15.333 --> 06:17.792
You will remove

06:15.333 --> 06:17.792
all the furniture from the room.

06:17.792 --> 06:19.000
The walls must be bare.

06:19.000 --> 06:20.417
I'm sure everything

06:19.000 --> 06:20.417
will be set up

06:20.417 --> 06:21.834
according to our

06:20.417 --> 06:21.834
specifications

06:21.834 --> 06:23.750
before the

06:21.834 --> 06:23.750
Legarans arrive.

06:23.750 --> 06:25.709
Isn't that

06:23.750 --> 06:25.709
right, Captain?

06:25.709 --> 06:28.291
I assure you, Ambassador,

06:25.709 --> 06:28.291
everything will be ready

06:28.291 --> 06:30.375
before the conference

06:28.291 --> 06:30.375
begins.

06:30.375 --> 06:31.917
My husband and I

06:31.917 --> 06:34.834
have every confidence

06:31.917 --> 06:34.834
in you, Captain.

06:34.834 --> 06:36.125
SAREK:

06:34.834 --> 06:36.125
I have worked

06:34.834 --> 06:36.125
for 93 years

06:36.125 --> 06:37.625
in preparation for this meeting.

06:37.625 --> 06:39.250
It is<i> vital</i>

06:39.250 --> 06:41.375
that no detail be overlooked.

06:41.375 --> 06:43.375
Perhaps we should

06:41.375 --> 06:43.375
allow these gentlemen

06:43.375 --> 06:45.792
to return to their

06:43.375 --> 06:45.792
work, Ambassador.

06:48.667 --> 06:50.291
That will be acceptable.

06:56.375 --> 06:59.208
These walls are too bright.

07:12.834 --> 07:14.875
The way Mendrossen

07:12.834 --> 07:14.875
described him,

07:14.875 --> 07:16.750
I expected to see

07:14.875 --> 07:16.750
a frail old man.

07:16.750 --> 07:20.000
I hope<i> I'm</i> that frail

07:16.750 --> 07:20.000
when I'm 202 years old.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.333
But his aides did seem

07:20.000 --> 07:22.333
to be a little...

07:22.333 --> 07:23.875
overprotective,

07:22.333 --> 07:23.875
didn't they?

07:23.875 --> 07:25.500
From what I could see,

07:25.500 --> 07:27.750
the Ambassador doesn't need

07:25.500 --> 07:27.750
protection from anything.

07:27.750 --> 07:30.542
Well, we'll respect

07:27.750 --> 07:30.542
Mr. Mendrossen's request

07:30.542 --> 07:34.417
and allow Ambassador

07:30.542 --> 07:34.417
Sarek his privacy.

07:34.417 --> 07:36.709
I suppose they were

07:34.417 --> 07:36.709
foolish and vain--

07:36.709 --> 07:38.834
my expectations of this voyage.

07:38.834 --> 07:42.417
Sharing his thoughts,

07:38.834 --> 07:42.417
memories,

07:42.417 --> 07:46.792
his unique understanding

07:42.417 --> 07:46.792
of the history he's made.

07:46.792 --> 07:49.750
Does this mean you're going to

07:46.792 --> 07:49.750
cancel the concert this evening?

07:49.750 --> 07:52.583
No, the concert

07:49.750 --> 07:52.583
will go ahead

07:49.750 --> 07:52.583
as scheduled.

07:52.583 --> 07:55.375
But it's a pity our guest

07:52.583 --> 07:55.375
of honor will be absent.

07:55.375 --> 07:56.875
For all we know,

07:55.375 --> 07:56.875
the Ambassador might enjoy

07:56.875 --> 07:58.291
an evening's

07:56.875 --> 07:58.291
entertainment.

07:58.291 --> 08:00.959
Why not ask his wife

07:58.291 --> 08:00.959
if she'd like to attend?

08:02.625 --> 08:05.792
That's an excellent

08:02.625 --> 08:05.792
idea, Counselor.

08:05.792 --> 08:08.333
You have the Bridge,

08:05.792 --> 08:08.333
Number One.

08:11.500 --> 08:14.041
(<i> door chimes</i> )

08:14.041 --> 08:16.000
Come in.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.208
PICARD:

08:16.000 --> 08:18.208
I hope I'm not intruding.

08:18.208 --> 08:19.834
Not at all, Captain.

08:19.834 --> 08:23.500
But Sarek is

08:19.834 --> 08:23.500
in meditation

08:19.834 --> 08:23.500
at the moment.

08:23.500 --> 08:26.166
Actually, I came

08:23.500 --> 08:26.166
to see you.

08:26.166 --> 08:29.000
Well, how nice.

08:29.000 --> 08:32.875
I so rarely get

08:29.000 --> 08:32.875
visitors of my own.

08:32.875 --> 08:36.250
Usually everyone wants

08:32.875 --> 08:36.250
to see the Ambassador.

08:36.250 --> 08:37.959
I find that

08:36.250 --> 08:37.959
hard to believe.

08:37.959 --> 08:39.542
Thank you.

08:41.583 --> 08:45.000
These quarters are

08:41.583 --> 08:45.000
quite comfortable.

08:45.000 --> 08:47.583
The Ambassador and I

08:45.000 --> 08:47.583
were very pleased

08:45.000 --> 08:47.583
when we heard

08:47.583 --> 08:50.291
that the negotiations

08:47.583 --> 08:50.291
were going to take place

08:50.291 --> 08:52.917
aboard the flagship

08:50.291 --> 08:52.917
of the Federation.

08:52.917 --> 08:54.458
The honor is ours.

08:54.458 --> 08:58.000
My husband has taken

08:54.458 --> 08:58.000
an interest in your career.

08:58.000 --> 09:01.959
He finds it to be...

08:58.000 --> 09:01.959
satisfactory.

09:01.959 --> 09:03.333
My word.

09:03.333 --> 09:05.417
High praise from a Vulcan.

09:05.417 --> 09:09.333
Some people who expect

09:05.417 --> 09:09.333
an emotional response

09:09.333 --> 09:11.125
often find Vulcans

09:09.333 --> 09:11.125
to be quite cold

09:11.125 --> 09:12.667
when they're merely being...

09:12.667 --> 09:14.166
Logical.

09:14.166 --> 09:16.250
Exactly.

09:16.250 --> 09:18.333
I came to invite you--

09:18.333 --> 09:21.500
and your husband,

09:18.333 --> 09:21.500
if he's available--

09:21.500 --> 09:24.500
to a Mozart recital

09:21.500 --> 09:24.500
this evening.

09:24.500 --> 09:27.250
What a tempting offer.

09:29.333 --> 09:33.208
I... doubt that the

09:29.333 --> 09:33.208
Ambassador will be

09:29.333 --> 09:33.208
able to attend,

09:33.208 --> 09:36.709
but I will make it

09:33.208 --> 09:36.709
a point to ask him.

09:36.709 --> 09:39.417
Well then,

09:36.709 --> 09:39.417
I hope to see you this evening.

09:39.417 --> 09:40.667
As do I.

09:54.625 --> 09:57.000
You are still

09:54.625 --> 09:57.000
unable to meditate?

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
It is of no importance.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.166
It has eluded you

09:59.000 --> 10:01.166
for many weeks.

10:01.166 --> 10:04.083
I said it is of

10:01.166 --> 10:04.083
no importance.

10:06.333 --> 10:08.166
You know I am right.

10:08.166 --> 10:11.625
My wife, you will

10:08.166 --> 10:11.625
leave me now.

10:11.625 --> 10:14.125
I require solitude.

10:22.375 --> 10:24.041
The temperature

10:22.375 --> 10:24.041
in the tank

10:24.041 --> 10:26.041
is now 150

10:24.041 --> 10:26.041
degrees Celsius.

10:26.041 --> 10:28.166
Okay, lock it off.

10:30.709 --> 10:31.750
Is that it?

10:31.750 --> 10:33.166
Can I get out

10:31.750 --> 10:33.166
of here now?

10:33.166 --> 10:34.750
What's your hurry?

10:34.750 --> 10:36.625
You don't really think

10:34.750 --> 10:36.625
anything's going to happen

10:36.625 --> 10:38.166
with Suzanne Dumont,

10:36.625 --> 10:38.166
do you?

10:38.166 --> 10:39.625
At least I'm not

10:38.166 --> 10:39.625
spending the night

10:39.625 --> 10:41.250
with a good book,

10:39.625 --> 10:41.250
like some people.

10:41.250 --> 10:42.583
What's that

10:41.250 --> 10:42.583
supposed to mean?

10:42.583 --> 10:43.959
Just what it sounds like.

10:43.959 --> 10:45.500
Let me tell

10:43.959 --> 10:45.500
you something.

10:45.500 --> 10:47.291
You'd get more action

10:45.500 --> 10:47.291
out of a good book

10:47.291 --> 10:49.166
than you'll ever

10:47.291 --> 10:49.166
see on this date,

10:47.291 --> 10:49.166
I'll guarantee it.

10:49.166 --> 10:51.417
She's not going to waste her

10:49.166 --> 10:51.417
time on someone like you.

10:51.417 --> 10:52.542
Someone like me?

10:52.542 --> 10:54.000
She's way out

10:52.542 --> 10:54.000
of your league.

10:54.000 --> 10:55.333
Since when did you become

10:54.000 --> 10:55.333
an expert on women?

10:55.333 --> 10:57.667
Compared to you, every

10:55.333 --> 10:57.667
male on this ship

10:57.667 --> 10:59.166
is an expert on women.

10:59.166 --> 11:00.375
Well, at least

10:59.166 --> 11:00.375
I don't have to find

11:00.375 --> 11:01.500
my women in a holodeck.

11:01.500 --> 11:02.959
What did you say?

11:01.500 --> 11:02.959
You heard me.

11:02.959 --> 11:04.542
Yeah, I heard you.

11:02.959 --> 11:04.542
Just what do you think...

11:04.542 --> 11:05.667
Something wrong?

11:10.917 --> 11:14.041
I asked a question.

11:14.041 --> 11:15.250
No, sir.

11:15.250 --> 11:17.375
Nothing wrong here.

11:17.375 --> 11:19.625
May I be excused,

11:17.375 --> 11:19.625
Commander?

11:23.792 --> 11:26.208
Anything you'd like

11:23.792 --> 11:26.208
to talk about, Geordi?

11:26.208 --> 11:28.208
No, sir.

11:37.083 --> 11:38.500
I noticed that

11:37.083 --> 11:38.500
Lieutenant Worf

11:38.500 --> 11:40.625
has put Ensign

11:38.500 --> 11:40.625
D'Amato on report

11:40.625 --> 11:42.625
for insubordination.

11:42.625 --> 11:44.166
D'Amato's been

11:42.625 --> 11:44.166
an exemplary officer.

11:44.166 --> 11:45.625
Indeed he has.

11:45.625 --> 11:47.083
Could you look into it,

11:45.625 --> 11:47.083
Number One?

11:45.625 --> 11:47.083
Of course.

11:47.083 --> 11:48.166
Good evening.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.166
Good evening.

11:49.166 --> 11:50.458
I assume that the work

11:50.458 --> 11:52.166
is progressing

11:50.458 --> 11:52.166
on the conference room.

11:52.166 --> 11:53.500
Yes, I checked in

11:53.500 --> 11:55.667
with Wesley and Geordi

11:53.500 --> 11:55.667
a few hours ago.

11:55.667 --> 11:57.542
There was a moment when

11:55.667 --> 11:57.542
I actually thought

11:57.542 --> 11:59.792
the two of them

11:57.542 --> 11:59.792
were going to

11:57.542 --> 11:59.792
hit each other.

