on behalf of the

12:09.917 --> 12:12.417
entire crew, welcome.

12:12.417 --> 12:14.208
It was my wife's suggestion

12:12.417 --> 12:14.208
that we attend.

12:14.208 --> 12:16.834
It seemed

12:14.208 --> 12:16.834
an ideal diversion.

12:16.834 --> 12:20.041
Perrin can be

12:16.834 --> 12:20.041
quite logical

12:20.041 --> 12:22.041
when she chooses.

12:22.041 --> 12:24.458
It seems that the Ambassador

12:22.041 --> 12:24.458
had more free time

12:24.458 --> 12:26.083
than I anticipated.

12:26.083 --> 12:27.875
Commander Data will be

12:27.875 --> 12:30.959
our featured soloist

12:27.875 --> 12:30.959
this evening.

12:32.000 --> 12:34.083
Data:

12:32.000 --> 12:34.083
I have been programmed

12:34.083 --> 12:36.583
to reproduce the individual

12:34.083 --> 12:36.583
musical styles

12:36.583 --> 12:38.375
of over 300 concert violinists

12:38.375 --> 12:41.625
including Heifetz, Menuhin,

12:38.375 --> 12:41.625
Grak-Tay, and Tataglia.

12:41.625 --> 12:43.667
Do you have a preference?

12:45.834 --> 12:47.709
Tataglia would be lovely.

12:47.709 --> 12:50.709
I hope you find

12:47.709 --> 12:50.709
the performance pleasing.

12:50.709 --> 12:52.959
I look forward to it.

12:52.959 --> 12:55.000
At your convenience, Mr. Data.

12:55.000 --> 12:56.166
Please.

13:07.125 --> 13:10.083
(<i> playing lively chamber music</i> )

